text.tspan: More than 20,000 street protests have occurred in America since January 15, 2017, spurred by mass shootings, immi
gration concerns, frustration with the president, and climate change. In the graphic below, each stripe represents a
topic, and the height of the stripes repre is determined by the number of related protests per month. Protests about
multiple topics are included in multiple stripes.

g.text: Crisis and scandal drive Americans to the street
